						               													<description>Amnesia is a card game that involves memory, thinking, and concentration. Each deck includes 58 cards and a rulebook.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to score the least amount of points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts with 4 cards, arranged on the table face-down on a 4x4 grid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players draw and discard cards, trying to achieve the lowest possible score based on card values. If a player discards a special card, its power is triggered.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The final round is triggered when a player believes they have 6 or less points on their cards, declaring &amp;quot;Amnesia!&amp;quot;. Each other player plays his last turn and the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who ended the game sum their cards points, and gets a bonus or penalty. The rest of the players sum its cards values for their score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Several rounds are played, until one player reaches 80 points on &amp;quot;classic&amp;quot; mode, or 40 for a &amp;quot;turbo&amp;quot; game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
